# 2b. Log into your Stripe dashboard (https://dashboard.stripe.com/) and include a screenshot of the payment page for the authorization you just created. 
# 2c. Use an API call to create a capture for $75. What happens to a charge if you only capture for a portion of an authorization, and not the full amount? 
# 2d. How do steps 2a-2c show on the customerâ€™s bank statement? 
# 2e. Name and describe 2 distinct business models/use cases that would require auth and then capture at a later time.


# 2a. create payment intent
// Set your secret key. Remember to switch to your live secret key in production.
// See your keys here: https://dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys
const stripe = require('stripe')('{{TEST_SECRET_KEY}}');

const paymentIntent = await stripe.paymentIntents.create({
  amount: 100,
  currency: 'usd',
});

##Result payment intent id: pi_3Sp0ZM2c6rQIzWO60bvyzctq
**associate with customer

# 2c. capture $75 
**needs to confirm first using with setting "off-session"==true. Otherwise, cannot confirm because automatic redirect is on

const stripe = require('stripe')('{{TEST_SECRET_KEY}}');

const paymentIntent = await stripe.paymentIntents.capture(
  'pi_3Sp0ZM2c6rQIzWO60bvyzctq',
  {
    amount_to_capture: 7500,
  }
);

##result: remaining $25 returned to customer

## 2d. When first authorized, statment will say $100 pending. With the actual charge, only $75 will show up with charged date on bank statement. The $100 will disappear when transaction takes place. 

